de.jannlab.core

Class CellType

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.jannlab.core.CellType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public final class CellType
extends Object
implements Serializable
    This class lists all standard cell types. Also individual cell types can be instantiated using the constructor.For each cell type several informations are given. On one hand these are functional specifications of the cell such as activation or integration function for both forward and backward pass. On the other hand these are some more meta informations, which are mainly used for debugging.

    Author:
    Sebastian Otte

      • SIGMOID

        public static final CellType SIGMOID
        A standard sigmoid with sum for integration. The enumeration instance represents on of the standard non-linear perceptrons.

      • SIGMOID2

      • TANH

        public static final CellType TANH
        A tanh cell with sum for integration. The enumeration instance represents on of the standard non-linear perceptrons.

      • LINEAR

        public static final CellType LINEAR
        A linear cell with id for activation and sum for integration. In this cell the error will just been passed though.

      • MULTIPLICATIVE

        public static final CellType MULTIPLICATIVE
        The multiplicative cell has an id activation and a product integration. The error in this cell will be just multiplied with the previous input. This is why this cell type regularly needs to be combined with DMULTIPLICATIVE cell to gain a correct gradient based error flow.

      • DMULTIPLICATIVE

        public static final CellType DMULTIPLICATIVE
        The dmultiplicative cells (delta correction) just pass the input of their the last incoming connection. In backward pass the divide the error by previous input (NaN are avoided). Regularly this cells is placed before each incoming connection to a multiplicative cell to gain a correct gradient based error flow.
